content: <metadata>   <idinfo>     <citation>       <citeinfo>         <origin>Office of Economic Development </origin>         <pubdate>20140407</pubdate>         <title>HUD Income Levels - 2013</title>         <geoform>vector digital data</geoform>       </citeinfo>     </citation>     <descript>       <abstract>The percentage of the 2013 population that is low-to-moderate income in each Census 2000 Block Group, as calculated by the US Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) is provided in this data layer. HUD uses 2000 Census boundaries to report their calculated data for 2013. For more information on HUD's methodology, visit: http://www.hud.gov/offices/cpd/systems/census/lowmod/index.cfmNote: Until HUD provides data in 2010 Census geographic boundaries, the City and County of Denver will not aggregate Block Group data to Tract or Neighborhood level.</abstract>       <purpose>Provides percentage of 2013 population that is low-to-moderate income in each Census 2000 Block Group, as calculated by the US Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD). </purpose>     </descript>     <status>       <update>As needed</update>     </status>     <spdom>       <bounding>         <westbc>-105.109967</westbc>         <eastbc>-104.599538</eastbc>         <northbc>39.914209</northbc>         <southbc>39.614313</southbc>       </bounding>     </spdom>     <keywords>       <theme>         <themekt>None</themekt>         <themekey>HUD-low-mod</themekey>         <themekey>low-to-moderate income</themekey>       </theme>       <theme>         <themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Categories</themekt>         <themekey>economy</themekey>       </theme>       <place>         <placekt>None</placekt>         <placekey>Denver</placekey>         <placekey>Denver County</placekey>         <placekey>Colorado</placekey>         <placekey>USA</placekey>       </place>     </keywords>     <accconst>None</accconst>     <useconst>ACCESS CONSTRAINTS:   None.
